== /facepalm ==

=== Basics ===

//Broadcasts your facepalm.//

**Usage:** /facepalm (player)

**Aliases:** /fp, /fpalm, /facep

**Permission Nodes**
 * rcmds.facepalm
 * rcmds.exempt.facepalm

=== In Depth ===

{{{/facepalm}}} sends a message to the server declaring that the sender has facepalmed. If {{{(player)}}} is specified,
the message will change to indicate that the sender is facepalming at {{{(player)}}}.

This command supports [[../name-completion.html|online name-completion]].

=== Examples ===

{{{/facepalm}}} - Shows a facepalm from the sender.\\
{{{/facepalm Notch}}} - Shows a facepalm towards {{{Notch}}} from the sender.